    stem: `A 6-year-old Indigenous boy presents to your practice in a rural area with purulent left ear discharge for the past 2 months. History and physical examination establish a diagnosis of chronic suppurative otitis media. Culture of the ear discharge is positive for pseudomonas aeruginosa. After ear toileting, which one of the following is the most appropriate treatment option to consider for this child?`,
