    id: "paeds-amedex-0027",
    topic: "Paediatrics",
    subtopic: "Duodenal atresia in Down syndrome",
    stem: `A male neonate born at 36 weeks gestation is noted to have many clinical features suggestive of Down syndrome. Six hours after birth, he starts vomiting. The vomit contains caseated milk and green material suggestive of bile. On examination, the abdomen is mildly distended. Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?`,
