    stem: `Emily, 18 months old, is brought to your clinic by her parents for a routine health visit. They are new to then town and this is the first time you visit her. She is the outcome of an uneventful pregnancy and has had no major medical problem so far. On examination, you hear a cardiac murmur. Which one of the following clinical findings suggests that the murmur is an innocent murmur?`,
