    stem: `A mother brings her 7-year-old son 6 days after eruption of a generalized rash that, based on the history and clinical findings, is found to be measles. She asks if her son is required to be excluded from school. She also mentions that according to the class teacher, all students in the class have complete vaccination against measles. Which one of the following would be the most appropriate advice regarding exclusion from school for this boy?`,
