    topic: "Paediatrics",
    subtopic: "Persistent proteinuria evaluation",
    stem: `An 8-year-old boy is found to have persistent proteinuria of 2+ on dipstick urine. There is no hematuria. Physical examination, including blood pressure, is unremarkable. Which one of the following is the next best investigation to consider for this boy?`,
