    topic: "Paediatrics",
    subtopic: "Immune thrombocytopenic purpura (ITP)",
    stem: `A 5-year-old boy is brought to your clinic with generalized petechial rash and bruises all over his body. He had an episode of upper respiratory tract infection (URTI) 3 weeks ago. On examination, he is otherwise healthy. His blood tests is only significant for a platelet count of 74,000/mm³. Red blood cells and white cells are within normal range. Which one of the following is the most appropriate management option in this child?`,
