    explanation: `This child is in infancy with a murmur. Although the murmur has characteristics of an innocent physiologic murmur (soft, short duration, systolic, limited to small area, low amplitude), referral to a pediatric cardiologist is indicated because murmurs in infancy, especially in the first 6 months, require specialist evaluation. The child is completely healthy with no associated physical findings suggestive of cardiac pathology, but the age warrants specialist assessment. Chest X-ray and ECG are of little value in assessment of murmurs in children and are not acceptable practice today. Simply reassuring parents without full evaluation by a specialist is inappropriate. Emergency echocardiography is not indicated. Telling parents the baby has heart disease without assessment is inappropriate.`,
