    id: "paeds-amedex-0091",
    topic: "Paediatrics",
    subtopic: "Legg-Calve-Perthes disease",
    stem: `A 4-year-old boy is brought to you with a painful left knee and limping. Recently, the child had a diagnosis of 'irritable hip'. On examination, internal rotation and abduction of the left hip joint is limited. An X-ray of the hip shows increased joint space. Which one of the following is the next best step in management?`,
