    stem: `A 9-year-old girl is brought to the pediatric clinic with a history of fever, fatigue, and a swollen lymph node in her right axilla. The mother reports that the family recently adopted a kitten. On examination, there is a tender, enlarged lymph node, and the girl has mild conjunctivitis in her right eye. Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in the diagnostic workup?`,
