    topic: "Paediatrics",
    subtopic: "Primary Nocturnal Enuresis",
    stem: `Ash, seven years old, has a diagnosis of primary nocturnal enuresis. He is going to a school camp in a few days, and his mother is concerned about his nocturia during the camp spray and wants to know what the best course of action is to prevent bedwetting while he is there. Which of the following would you advise as the most appropriate option?`,
