    id: "paeds-amedex-0104",
    topic: "Paediatrics",
    subtopic: "Lobar pneumonia in infants",
    stem: `A 2-year-old boy is brought to the Emergency Department by his parents, who are concerned about his fever and difficulty breathing. The fever has started this afternoon. On examination, he looks ill and pale and is grunting. He has a temperature of 39.6°C and his respiration is shallow with a rate of 38 breaths per minute. Chest auscultation is normal. Which one of following could be the most likely diagnosis?`,
